  "title": "MANAGER – MOTOR CLAIMS SECTION",
  "description": "<h3><em>Job Duties:</em></h3><ul><li>Assist overseas' group companies in claims operation, particularly motor claims.</li><li>Monitor claims trend of group companies and create counter measures for significantly high claims.</li><li>Conduct on-site claims survey and claims audit on overseas’ group companies.</li><li>Assist in investigating/negotiating the settlement of complex or contentious claims.</li><li>Provide advice, when necessary, on underwriting decisions for new and existing business based on claims handling experience.</li><li>Provide value-added services and information based on claims handling experience while accompanying marketing activities.</li><li>Assist in the development and implementation of claims management programmes that deliver maximum cost savings to the company.</li><li>Provide and conduct training for overseas’ claims staff when necessary.</li><li>Overseas’ business travels are required.</li></ul><h3><em>Requirements:</em></h3><ul><li>University Degree with professional insurance qualifications.</li><li>At least 5 years of motor claims experience in an insurance company.</li><li>Work experience in international loss adjusting company and/or in a regional capacity.</li><li>Analytical with good report writing, presentation and communication skills.</li><li>Proficiency in Japanese language is required to liaise with Japan HQ and to read Japanese reports/documents.</li><li>Good written report, presentation and communication skills in both English and Japanese language.</li></ul>",
